🚀 Release Notes

This release introduces a Streamlit-powered interactive search application for exploring beauty product reviews using BM25 and Semantic Search techniques.

The system enables users to input a natural language query and choose between:

🔍 BM25 (keyword-based retrieval)
🧠 Semantic Search (embedding-based retrieval)

Based on the selected mode, the application retrieves the most relevant products from the dataset and displays:

Product details
Associated review text extracted from the underlying review corpus
Retrieval score for transparency of ranking relevance
💡 Key Features
⚡ Dual search engine support: BM25 + Semantic Search
🖥️ Interactive Streamlit web interface
🔎 Query-based product retrieval system
📄 Automatic fetching of reviews from the dataset
👍👎 User feedback collection for each result
💾 Persistent feedback storage in feedback.csv for future analysis
📊 Overview

This project demonstrates how traditional information retrieval (BM25) and modern embedding-based semantic search can be combined to enhance product discovery in a real-world dataset of beauty product reviews.

📁 Output
Search results ranked by relevance
Review snippets for retrieved products
User feedback logging in feedback.csv

